    "ExtraInfo": "If no slot is specified, the command returns mounted file systems for the active RP.This command allows you to ascertain the presence or absence of specific system mounts. For example, this command might be used to determine /tmp-related mounts, which are used to create many run-time directories and files.Users may be requested to execute this command to collect information about the underlying configuration of the platform software.The RP output can differ depending on how the router was booted, and whether there are USB devices inserted.The SIP and ESP output can differ depending on whether the chassis is a dual or single RP.",
